FBIS4-60683 "drnes103_l_94022" FBIS-NES-94-103 Daily Report 25 May 1994 ISRAEL Vatican Accepts Indirect Responsibility for Holocaust Vatican Accepts Indirect Responsibility for Holocaust TA2505105994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 25 May 94 TA2505105994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el English BFN [Excerpts] First to the dramatic disclosure that Israel and the Vatican are formulating an agreement in which the Catholic Church accepts indirect responsibility for anti-Semitism from ancient times up to the Holocaust. We have more details in this report from Dick Winter: [Begin Winter recording] The historic agreement, which was drafted by an interreligious commission from Israel and the Vatican, states that a frightful mixture of racism, along with religious, political, social, and economic hostility against the Jewish people throughout history, created the basis for the Holocaust, and the Catholic Church did not do enough to oppose it. One of the chief Israeli members of the commission, Rabbi David Rosen, says the draft is a major achievement and that the Vatican goes farther than even he ever expected it to go. [passage omitted] Also in the document: the Vatican's acceptance of responsibility for creating in its teachings an atmosphere of hatred toward the Jewish people. Rabbi Rosen says he believes that the draft agreement will now be endorsed by the Pope. [end recording]
